
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hp-logcapture` baraye gereftan va zakhire kardane log az dastgah haye HP (mesle printer-ha) estefade mishavad.  In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad moshkelate dastgah ra peygiri va debug konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor va gozine-haye mojud.
    🔹 `--debug` --> 🐞  Ezafe kardane etela'at debug be log-ha baraye tahlil bishtar.
    🔹 `--file=<filename>` --> 💾 Zakhire kardane log-ha dar yek file ba name `<filename>`. Agar esm file ra nadehid, be soorate pishfarz dar terminal chap mishavad.
    🔹 `--duration=<seconds>` --> ⏱️  Modat zamani ke log-ha gerefte mishavand (be saniye).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hp-logcapture

    🔹 Gereftan log az dastgah pishfarz HP va chap kardane an dar terminal.

    $ hp-logcapture --file=myprinter.log --duration=60

    🔹 Gereftan log az dastgah pishfarz HP be modat 60 saniye va zakhire kardane an dar file "myprinter.log".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hp-logcapture --help

    🔹 Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor `hp-logcapture`, ke hameye gozine-ha va tarze estefade az an ra neshan midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hp-logcapture` command is used to capture and save logs from HP devices (such as printers). It helps you track and debug device problems.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Display the command's help message and available options.
    🔹 `--debug` --> 🐞 Add debugging information to the logs for more detailed analysis.
    🔹 `--file=<filename>` --> 💾 Save the logs to a file named `<filename>`. If no filename is provided, the logs are printed to the terminal by default.
    🔹 `--duration=<seconds>` --> ⏱️ The duration for which logs are captured (in seconds).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hp-logcapture

    🔹 Capture logs from the default HP device and print them to the terminal.

    $ hp-logcapture --file=myprinter.log --duration=60

    🔹 Capture logs from the default HP device for 60 seconds and save them to the file "myprinter.log".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hp-logcapture --help

    🔹 Displays the help message for the `hp-logcapture` command, showing all available options and how to use them.

